Insight Dashboard


Business Request:

The client wants a sales report dashboard based on the provided data.


Data Cleansing & Transformation (SQL):

To create the necessary data model for analysing and fulfilling the business’s needs, a group of tables were extracted using SQL from the data provided. One data source (sales budgets) was provided in Excel format and was connected to the data model later in the process. Below are the SQL statements for cleansing and transforming necessary data.

 -- Cleaned the DIM table to grab dates after 2018
  SELECT datekey,
         fulldatealternatekey      AS date,
         englishdaynameofweek      AS day,
         englishmonthname          AS month,
         LEFT(englishmonthname, 3) AS month_short,
         monthnumberofyear         AS monthNum,
         calendarquarter           AS quarter,
         calendaryear              AS year
  FROM   dimdate
  WHERE  calendaryear >= 2018;
  
  --get customer information
  SELECT c.customerkey,
         c.firstname,
         c.lastname,
         c.firstname + ' ' + c.lastname AS FullName,
         CASE c.gender
           WHEN 'M' THEN 'Male'
           WHEN 'F' THEN 'Female'
         END                            AS gender,
         c.datefirstpurchase,
         g.city                         AS customerCity
  FROM   dimcustomer AS c
         LEFT JOIN dimgeography AS g
                ON g.geographykey = c.geographykey
  ORDER  BY customerkey;
  
  
  -- get products table
   SELECT p.productkey,
         p.productalternatekey            AS productItemCode,
         p.englishproductname             AS productName,
         ps.englishproductsubcategoryname AS subCatagory,
         pc.englishproductcategoryname    AS productCatagory,
         p.color                          AS productColo,
         p.size                           AS productSize,
         p.productline,
         p.modelname                      AS productModel,
         p.englishdescription             AS productDescription,
         Isnull (p.status, 'outdated')    AS productStatus
  FROM   dimproduct AS p
         LEFT JOIN dimproductsubcategory AS ps
                ON ps.productsubcategorykey = p.productsubcategorykey
         LEFT JOIN dimproductcategory AS pc
                ON ps.productcategorykey = pc.productcategorykey
  ORDER  BY p.productkey;
  
  -- get internet sales data
   SELECT productkey,
         orderdatekey,
         duedatekey,
         shipdatekey,
         customerkey,
         salesordernumber,
         orderquantity,
         unitprice,
         unitpricediscountpct,
         totalproductcost,
         salesamount
  FROM   factinternetsales
  WHERE  LEFT(orderdatekey, 4) >= Year(Getdate()) - 4
  ORDER  BY orderdatekey

Sales Management Dashboard:

The finished sales management dashboard’s first page works as a dashboard overview. The two other pages focus on combining tables for necessary details and visualizations to show sales over time, per customer and per product.
